{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a2379bb1-b5c7-4145-b699-84b9fb6e07d4","content":"The most likely issue is that **.NET MAUI's Android build tooling does NOT use the `JAVA_HOME` environment variable** by default. It has its own JDK resolution logic that prioritizes the workload-bundled Microsoft OpenJDK over your system JDK.\n\n**Fix options:**\n\n1. **Install/repair the workload's bundled JDK** (recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet workload repair\n   ```\n\n2. **Or explicitly point the build to your Temurin JDK** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <JavaSdkDirectory>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home</JavaSdkDirectory>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Or set it via environment** (supported in newer .NET SDKs):\n   ```bash\n   export DOTNET_ANDROID_JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home\n   ```\n\nIf you share the exact error message, I can narrow it down further.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ebad4bda-bf17-4f4b-93b7-bef85b09742a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure with a Java-related error on macOS. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed and JAVA_HOME points to it.\n\nThis is a known issue with .NET MAUI / Xamarin Android builds. The problem is likely that the .NET Android SDK has specific requirements for the Java JDK version and path.\n\nLet me think about common issues:\n\n1. **.NET 8+ MAUI requires JDK 17** - they have that, so version isn't the issue.\n2. **JAVA_HOME path on macOS** - On macOS, the Adoptium Temurin JDK is typically installed at `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home`. The user needs to make sure JAVA_HOME points to the correct path.\n\n\n3. **.NET's Android SDK has its own JDK bundled** - Since .NET 6+, the Android workload installs Microsoft OpenJDK, and the build system might be using that instead of respecting the JAVA_HOME enviro